title: California Importer Recalls Salami Products That Were Not Presented To USDA for Reinspection
summary: WASHINGTON, Oct. 26, 2013 Ferrarini USA, Importer of Record in San Fernando, Calif., is recalling approximately 13,118 pounds of salami products that were not presented for import reinspection, the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
